2025-09-12 08:21:49 [INFO] [GAME] You've started a new quest: <col=081190>Mourning's End Part I</col>
2025-09-12 08:21:49 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:21:51 [INFO] [GAME] You have unlocked a new music track: <col=e00a19>Far Away
2025-09-12 08:21:51 [INFO] LOADING
2025-09-12 08:21:53 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:21:54 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:21:54 [INFO] Can continue: Eluned
2025-09-12 08:21:54 [INFO] Can continue: Here you go... If you ever need to get back to Lletya,<br>you can use this.
2025-09-12 08:21:54 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:21:55 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:21:55 [INFO] Can continue: Eluned
2025-09-12 08:21:55 [INFO] Can continue: Use it sparingly as it only has a few uses. If you need,<br>I can re-enchant it, but I am not as talented as the<br>singer who originally made this one.
2025-09-12 08:21:55 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:21:57 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:21:57 [INFO] Can continue: PLAYER_NAME
2025-09-12 08:21:57 [INFO] Can continue: Thanks a lot Eluned!
2025-09-12 08:21:57 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:21:58 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:21:58 [INFO] Can continue: Eluned
2025-09-12 08:21:58 [INFO] Can continue: Now, I had better get going or Islwyn will get worried.
2025-09-12 08:21:58 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:21:59 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:21:59 [INFO] Can continue: Arianwyn
2025-09-12 08:21:59 [INFO] Can continue: Ah PLAYER_NAME, glad to see you made it. Welcome to<br>Lletya, home to the Elven Resistance.
2025-09-12 08:21:59 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:22:00 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:22:00 [INFO] Can continue: PLAYER_NAME
2025-09-12 08:22:00 [INFO] Can continue: Thank you. It wasn't particularly easy to get here, it<br>took some work to convince Islwyn I could be trusted.
2025-09-12 08:22:00 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:22:01 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:22:01 [INFO] Can continue: Arianwyn
2025-09-12 08:22:01 [INFO] Can continue: That is not surprising, he is not particularly fond of<br>humans. But if you've earnt his trust, it proves to me<br>that I was right to take a chance on you.
2025-09-12 08:22:01 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:22:02 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:22:02 [INFO] Can continue: PLAYER_NAME
2025-09-12 08:22:02 [INFO] Can continue: I'm glad you did. I hate the thought that I might still be<br>blindly working for King Lathas and Lord Iorwerth<br>right now.
2025-09-12 08:22:02 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:22:04 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:22:04 [INFO] Can continue: Arianwyn
2025-09-12 08:22:04 [INFO] Can continue: Well you're here now and you still have a chance to<br>right your previous wrongs.
2025-09-12 08:22:04 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:22:05 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:22:05 [INFO] Can continue: PLAYER_NAME
2025-09-12 08:22:05 [INFO] Can continue: I hope so. There's a lot I still don't understand though.<br>Why are King Lathas and Lord Iorwerth working<br>together? Where does the plague fit in?
2025-09-12 08:22:05 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:22:06 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:22:06 [INFO] Can continue: Arianwyn
2025-09-12 08:22:06 [INFO] Can continue: I'm afraid that a lot is still unknown to us as well.<br>However, I will explain what I can. Be aware that this is<br>only a brief overview. You'll find some books around the<br>village that explain more if you wish though.
2025-09-12 08:22:06 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:22:07 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:22:07 [INFO] ===
2025-09-12 08:22:07 [INFO] Okay, let's begin.
2025-09-12 08:22:07 [INFO] Let's skip the backstory.
2025-09-12 08:22:07 [INFO] ===
2025-09-12 08:22:07 [INFO] 1895 Option: 1 Okay, let's begin.
2025-09-12 08:22:08 [INFO] [GAME] <col=8f4808>Your stamina enhancement is about to expire.</col>
2025-09-12 08:22:11 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:22:11 [INFO] Can continue: PLAYER_NAME
2025-09-12 08:22:11 [INFO] Can continue: Okay, let's begin.
2025-09-12 08:22:11 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:22:12 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:22:12 [INFO] Can continue: Arianwyn
2025-09-12 08:22:12 [INFO] Can continue: Many years ago, all elves lived in harmony within the<br>crystal city of Prifddinas alongside our goddess, Seren.
2025-09-12 08:22:12 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:22:13 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:22:13 [INFO] Can continue: Arianwyn
2025-09-12 08:22:13 [INFO] Can continue: When the God Wars ended, Seren was lost to us. For<br>the first time, we were alone. To lead us through those<br>difficult times, Baxtorian Cadarn was named the first<br>king of the elves.
2025-09-12 08:22:13 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:22:14 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:22:14 [INFO] Can continue: Arianwyn
2025-09-12 08:22:14 [INFO] Can continue: Under Baxtorian, our kingdom expanded into the east.<br>We prospered for a time, but little did we know that an<br>enemy walked among us.
2025-09-12 08:22:14 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:22:16 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:22:16 [INFO] Can continue: Arianwyn
2025-09-12 08:22:16 [INFO] Can continue: During that time, Lord Iorwerth turned away from<br>Seren and pledged himself to Zamorak, the Dark Lord.
2025-09-12 08:22:16 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:22:16 [INFO] LAG DETECTED 770ms
2025-09-12 08:22:17 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:22:17 [INFO] Can continue: Arianwyn
2025-09-12 08:22:17 [INFO] Can continue: A larger kingdom meant our forces were further<br>spread. Lord Iorwerth took advantage of that. He<br>claimed Prifddinas as his own.
2025-09-12 08:22:17 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:22:18 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:22:18 [INFO] Can continue: Arianwyn
2025-09-12 08:22:18 [INFO] Can continue: Baxtorian tried to take it back from him, but Prifddinas<br>was built to survive the God Wars. There was no way<br>to retake it.
2025-09-12 08:22:18 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:22:19 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:22:19 [INFO] Can continue: Arianwyn
2025-09-12 08:22:19 [INFO] Can continue: In a last attempt to keep the city safe, Baxtorian and<br>the clan elders sung the song of inversion which<br>reverted the entire city into a crystal seed.
2025-09-12 08:22:19 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:22:20 [INFO] [GAME] <col=8f4808>Your stamina enhancement has expired.</col>
2025-09-12 08:22:21 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:22:21 [INFO] Can continue: PLAYER_NAME
2025-09-12 08:22:21 [INFO] Can continue: Ah, so that explains why the city just looks like an<br>empty field.
2025-09-12 08:22:21 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:22:22 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:22:22 [INFO] Can continue: Arianwyn
2025-09-12 08:22:22 [INFO] Can continue: Indeed. After that, Baxtorian returned to the east but<br>found that the rest of the kingdom had fallen while he<br>was away. Not only that, but his wife, Glarial, had been<br>taken.
2025-09-12 08:22:22 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:22:23 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:22:23 [INFO] Can continue: PLAYER_NAME
2025-09-12 08:22:23 [INFO] Can continue: I know this bit, Baxtorian retreated into his home<br>beneath the waterfall and never came out. I moved<br>Glarial's remains into the waterfall so they could be<br>together.
2025-09-12 08:22:23 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:22:24 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:22:24 [INFO] Can continue: Arianwyn
2025-09-12 08:22:24 [INFO] Can continue: That's good to hear, I can see why you managed to<br>earn Islwyn's trust.
2025-09-12 08:22:24 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:22:25 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:22:25 [INFO] Can continue: Arianwyn
2025-09-12 08:22:25 [INFO] Can continue: Anyway, with Baxtorian gone and Prifddinas lost, our<br>land erupted into a Civil War. We've been fighting ever<br>since.
2025-09-12 08:22:25 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:22:27 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:22:27 [INFO] Can continue: PLAYER_NAME
2025-09-12 08:22:27 [INFO] Can continue: I see, it's good to have a bit more understanding. But<br>where does King Lathas come into this?
2025-09-12 08:22:27 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:22:28 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:22:28 [INFO] Can continue: Arianwyn
2025-09-12 08:22:28 [INFO] Can continue: That is the bit we're not so sure on. We know little<br>about the lands to the east. From what we can tell, it<br>seems that Lord Iorwerth has promised to support King<br>Lathas in reclaiming some land his family once owned.
2025-09-12 08:22:28 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:22:30 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:22:30 [INFO] Can continue: PLAYER_NAME
2025-09-12 08:22:30 [INFO] Can continue: But why? What's in it for Lord Iorwerth.
2025-09-12 08:22:30 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:22:31 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:22:31 [INFO] Can continue: Arianwyn
2025-09-12 08:22:31 [INFO] Can continue: That's what we want you to find out. According to our<br>spies, Lord Iorwerth has used the alliance with King<br>Lathas as an opportunity to infiltrate West Ardougne.<br>The city must contain something he needs.
2025-09-12 08:22:31 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:22:32 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:22:32 [INFO] Can continue: PLAYER_NAME
2025-09-12 08:22:32 [INFO] Can continue: Infiltrate? How?
2025-09-12 08:22:32 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:22:33 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:22:33 [INFO] Can continue: Arianwyn
2025-09-12 08:22:33 [INFO] Can continue: Those that you know as mourners are in fact elves in<br>service to Lord Iorwerth. We regularly see them<br>crossing the Arandar mountain pass and into the east.
2025-09-12 08:22:33 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:22:34 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:22:34 [INFO] Can continue: PLAYER_NAME
2025-09-12 08:22:34 [INFO] Can continue: Mourners are elves?
2025-09-12 08:22:34 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:22:35 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:22:35 [INFO] Can continue: Arianwyn
2025-09-12 08:22:35 [INFO] Can continue: That they are. We assume that the plague is a cover<br>up for them to enter the city unchallenged. We don't<br>know why though. That's why we need you.
2025-09-12 08:22:35 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:22:37 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:22:37 [INFO] Can continue: Arianwyn
2025-09-12 08:22:37 [INFO] Can continue: You know the city and can freely travel there. You are<br>the perfect person for this task. We need you to go to<br>West Ardougne, infiltrate the mourners and find out<br>what they are doing in the city.
2025-09-12 08:22:37 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:22:38 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:22:38 [INFO] Can continue: PLAYER_NAME
2025-09-12 08:22:38 [INFO] Can continue: So you want me to infiltrate the mourners? How am I<br>supposed to achieve that?
2025-09-12 08:22:38 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:22:39 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:22:39 [INFO] Can continue: Arianwyn
2025-09-12 08:22:39 [INFO] Can continue: I don't have an exact plan for you I'm afraid. You<br>know the city better than any of us so are best placed<br>to make a plan yourself.
