2025-09-12 08:28:58 [INFO] Talking to Essyllt
2025-09-12 08:28:58 [INFO] Interacting Essyllt Talk-to
2025-09-12 08:29:01 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:29:01 [INFO] Can continue: PLAYER_NAME
2025-09-12 08:29:01 [INFO] Can continue: Hello, I'm...
2025-09-12 08:29:01 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:29:01 [INFO] ANTIBAN: mouse_off_screen
2025-09-12 08:29:03 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:29:03 [INFO] Can continue: Essyllt
2025-09-12 08:29:03 [INFO] Can continue: Ah... I take it you are one of the new recruits?
2025-09-12 08:29:03 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:29:04 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:29:04 [INFO] Can continue: PLAYER_NAME
2025-09-12 08:29:04 [INFO] Can continue: Well I'm...
2025-09-12 08:29:04 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:29:05 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:29:05 [INFO] Can continue: Essyllt
2025-09-12 08:29:05 [INFO] Can continue: I'm Essyllt and I'm in charge here. Now come on, let<br>us have a look at your paper work.
2025-09-12 08:29:05 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:29:06 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:29:06 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:29:07 [INFO] [GAME] <col=8f4808>Your stamina enhancement is about to expire.</col>
2025-09-12 08:29:07 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:29:07 [INFO] Can continue: Essyllt
2025-09-12 08:29:07 [INFO] Can continue: This seems to be all in order. Welcome to the Death<br>Guard. Now, for your first assignment...
2025-09-12 08:29:07 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:29:08 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:29:08 [INFO] Can continue: Essyllt
2025-09-12 08:29:08 [INFO] Can continue: As you may know, part of what we do here is keep the<br>people believing in the plague...
2025-09-12 08:29:08 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:29:10 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:29:10 [INFO] Can continue: PLAYER_NAME
2025-09-12 08:29:10 [INFO] Can continue: Why?
2025-09-12 08:29:10 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:29:11 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:29:11 [INFO] Can continue: Essyllt
2025-09-12 08:29:11 [INFO] Can continue: Did they not tell you? Hmm... I'd better fill you in.
2025-09-12 08:29:11 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:29:12 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:29:12 [INFO] Can continue: Essyllt
2025-09-12 08:29:12 [INFO] Can continue: Well as you undoubtedly know, we were sent here by<br>Lord Iorwerth to secure the city. The reason for this is<br>so that we can access the caves below...
2025-09-12 08:29:12 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:29:13 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:29:13 [INFO] Can continue: PLAYER_NAME
2025-09-12 08:29:13 [INFO] Can continue: What's important about the caves?
2025-09-12 08:29:13 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:29:14 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:29:14 [INFO] Can continue: Essyllt
2025-09-12 08:29:14 [INFO] Can continue: I'm afraid that information is classified until you prove<br>your commitment to the Death Guard.
2025-09-12 08:29:14 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:29:15 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:29:15 [INFO] Can continue: PLAYER_NAME
2025-09-12 08:29:15 [INFO] Can continue: Oh, fair enough.
2025-09-12 08:29:15 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:29:16 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:29:16 [INFO] Can continue: Essyllt
2025-09-12 08:29:16 [INFO] Can continue: Now, to keep our presence in the city secret, Lord<br>Iorwerth arranged an alliance with King Lathas, the<br>ruler in the east.
2025-09-12 08:29:16 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:29:17 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:29:17 [INFO] Can continue: Essyllt
2025-09-12 08:29:17 [INFO] Can continue: Apparently the fool thinks we will help him dispose of the<br>Knights of Camelot once our work here is done. I<br>expect he'll be disappointed.
2025-09-12 08:29:17 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:29:19 [INFO] [GAME] <col=8f4808>Your stamina enhancement has expired.</col>
2025-09-12 08:29:19 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:29:19 [INFO] Can continue: Essyllt
2025-09-12 08:29:19 [INFO] Can continue: Anyway, the plague serves two purposes. First, it allows<br>us to move around the city in secret thanks to our<br>mourner disguises.
2025-09-12 08:29:19 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:29:20 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:29:20 [INFO] Can continue: Essyllt
2025-09-12 08:29:20 [INFO] Can continue: Second, it means we can abduct citizens to mine the<br>caves below with ease. We just pretend they've fallen<br>victim to the plague.
2025-09-12 08:29:20 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:29:22 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:29:22 [INFO] Can continue: PLAYER_NAME
2025-09-12 08:29:22 [INFO] Can continue: Doesn't anyone suspect the truth?
2025-09-12 08:29:22 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:29:23 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:29:23 [INFO] Can continue: Essyllt
2025-09-12 08:29:23 [INFO] Can continue: Well we have had a few near misses. Recently we had<br>some girl from East Ardougne poking around asking<br>too many questions, so we locked her up while we<br>decided what to do with her.
2025-09-12 08:29:23 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:29:24 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:29:24 [INFO] Can continue: Essyllt
2025-09-12 08:29:24 [INFO] Can continue: Annoyingly, she managed to escape with the help of<br>some adventurer. Lucky for us, they were so stupid<br>that we managed to use the adventurer to deal with<br>King Tyras. It all worked out quite well in the end.
2025-09-12 08:29:24 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:29:25 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:29:25 [INFO] Can continue: Essyllt
2025-09-12 08:29:25 [INFO] Can continue: Things like that is why we must ensure the people keep<br>believing in the plague though. One of the things we do<br>to keep up the lie is to fool old Farmer Brumty into<br>believing his sheep are infected.
2025-09-12 08:29:25 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:29:26 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:29:26 [INFO] Can continue: Essyllt
2025-09-12 08:29:26 [INFO] Can continue: The old halfwit thinks just because his sheep are an<br>abnormal colour, that they are all ill with plague. It's<br>amazing what a bit of dye can do.
2025-09-12 08:29:26 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:29:27 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:29:27 [INFO] Can continue: PLAYER_NAME
2025-09-12 08:29:27 [INFO] Can continue: You dyed them?
2025-09-12 08:29:27 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:29:28 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:29:28 [INFO] Can continue: Essyllt
2025-09-12 08:29:28 [INFO] Can continue: Well you don't think they end up those ridiculous<br>colours naturally do you?
2025-09-12 08:29:28 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:29:29 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:29:29 [INFO] Can continue: Essyllt
2025-09-12 08:29:29 [INFO] Can continue: Anyway, shame of it is that we have yet to find a way<br>to stop the dye from washing out. So we need someone,<br>that someone being you, to go and re-dye them.
2025-09-12 08:29:29 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:29:31 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:29:31 [INFO] Can continue: PLAYER_NAME
2025-09-12 08:29:31 [INFO] Can continue: Simple enough, you want me to give a blue rinse to a<br>load of old sheep?
2025-09-12 08:29:31 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:29:33 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:29:33 [INFO] Can continue: Essyllt
2025-09-12 08:29:33 [INFO] Can continue: Not quite, for starters the sheep need to be dyed red,<br>yellow, green and blue. But most important is that you<br>are not seen doing this by anyone.
2025-09-12 08:29:33 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:29:34 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:29:34 [INFO] Can continue: Essyllt
2025-09-12 08:29:34 [INFO] Can continue: Also you will need to re-dye them the colours they<br>already are or the farmer may notice the change.
2025-09-12 08:29:34 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:29:35 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:29:35 [INFO] Can continue: PLAYER_NAME
2025-09-12 08:29:35 [INFO] Can continue: That sounds a little more tricky. How did you do it<br>before?
2025-09-12 08:29:35 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:29:36 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:29:36 [INFO] Can continue: Essyllt
2025-09-12 08:29:36 [INFO] Can continue: We have a gnomic device that fires fat dye parcels that<br>rupture on impact.
2025-09-12 08:29:36 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:29:37 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:29:37 [INFO] Can continue: Essyllt
2025-09-12 08:29:37 [INFO] Can continue: Unfortunately, we have run out of the parcels and the<br>device is broken.
2025-09-12 08:29:37 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:29:38 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:29:38 [INFO] Can continue: PLAYER_NAME
2025-09-12 08:29:38 [INFO] Can continue: Can I take a look at it?
2025-09-12 08:29:38 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:29:40 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:29:40 [INFO] Can continue: Essyllt
2025-09-12 08:29:40 [INFO] Can continue: Sure. We have a gnome inventor here too. Sadly, he is<br>not being very helpful about fixing it, but you can talk<br>to him if you like. Here is the key, he is in the next<br>room. And here's the device as well.
2025-09-12 08:29:40 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 08:29:41 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 08:29:41 [INFO] Can continue: Essyllt hands you a strange object and a tarnished key.
2025-09-12 08:29:41 [INFO] Continue
